# MAUS Public Roadmap (Non-TS)

This roadmap outlines the *public, non-technical* progression of MAUS.  
It focuses on visible user-facing milestones while protecting the internal architecture, algorithms, TS systems, and proprietary concepts that power the project.

---

## 🚀 1. Genesis Layer — The First MAUS Environment  
The foundational entry space into MAUS.  
A minimal, interactive, future-ready environment establishing presence inside the MAUS ecosystem.

---

## 🔐 2. Identity Layer — Secure, User-Controlled Identity  
A privacy-first identity framework ensuring users control how they appear, move, and exist inside MAUS.  
All internal mechanics remain private and off-chain for security.

---

## 🛠️ 3. Sandbox Creator Tools — Build Your Own World  
Tools enabling early creation of personal rooms, creative spaces, and prototype MAUS environments.  
No internal engine or technical implementation is disclosed.

---

## 🌐 4. Network Presence — Live, Persistent Existence  
Early support for movement, visibility, and the feeling of “being there” inside MAUS.  
This represents high-level progress without exposing network protocols or system design.

---

## ⚙️ 5. MAUS Engine 0.1 — The Prototype Layer  
A protected, foundational engine powering navigation and interaction within MAUS.  
Public details remain conceptual only; all internals are confidential.

---

## 📌 Notes  
- This roadmap shares only *public-facing vision*, not internal engineering.  
- TS systems, cryptographic layers, dimensional architecture, routing logic, and OS-level pipeline remain confidential.  
- New milestones will be added as progress becomes publicly shareable. 
